This paper deals with type systems for information flow control, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses logical relation models, which are commonly used in the verification of programming languages (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the translation between two different labeling granularities, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and systems (cs.SY).
